<TITLE> RAB nabs fake major </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion on Sunday arrested four frauds for cheating people with false identity, from Khilkhet and Uttara in Dhaka. The four arrested are Md Hafizur Rahman, 43, Md Abu Nasir Hawlader, 60, and Jashim, 25, and Salauddin Monu, 40. They have cheating people for a long time. Three of them pretended to be army officers while another pretended to be a customs officer. Victims accused that the frauds had earned a lot of money cheating people. RAB-1 officer Md Zahirul Islam told bdnews24.com that Hafiz and Nasir were arrested on prior information from Khilkhet Nikunja area. Meanwhile, the police were informed that another man near Turag was also cheating people in the guise of an army captain. A victim also filed a general diary with the Turag police. On information, the fake captain Jashim and his associate Salauddin were arrested from Falguni Restaurant beside Abdullahpur's Tahsin Filling Station at Uttara Police will take legal action against them, Zahirul said. bdnew
